                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210110-16-off95 t18210110-16-crimeloc97"></join>. On the 29th of December, about half-past nine o'clock, I heard a disturbance, and found a pane of glass cut.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182101100011"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18210110-16-person193">
                  RICHARD 
                  CRESSY
               <interp inst="t18210110-16-person193" type="surname" value="CRESSY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-16-person193" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-16-person193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , I live next door to Mr. Machin. I was standing at the door, and saw the prisoner standing at Mr. Machin's with another person; I suspected and watched them. A person passed by, and said,</p>
               <p>"They have cut the window!" - they then went away. The prisoner was standing leaning on the window where the glass was cut. I did not see him do any thing. He was crossing the road and I secured him.</p>
               <p>
